Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.07,0:00:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to be here. This is an erudite audience. Erudite. That's their trouble. That's their trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.67,0:00:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intellect, which informs us of spiritual reality. First of all, for eons, we're the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.37,0:00:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,animal. Then we learn how to think. Then through thinking, we learn that there is a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.63,0:01:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. And then we decide we are interested in that higher awareness. We become spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.50,0:01:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,involved. And then the intellect, which was a friend to us to inform us about it, bring
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.26,0:01:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,us here, becomes the trap. It becomes that which attracted us now becomes what we become
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.94,0:01:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,mired in. So the essential to the intellect and reason and logic is the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.49,0:01:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality, which is the obstacle to a group like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.77,0:01:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is not an obstacle. Willingness to love. Motivation. So it becomes, the intellect then
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.67,0:02:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the trap. How to transcend the dualistic structure of the ego. Essential to the ego's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.36,0:02:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dominion is the Newtonian belief in causality. And therefore, we'll start out with the end
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.91,0:02:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move back to the beginning. There's only one thing you need to learn from the whole lecture today. The reasons for it, we will go over. There is nothing causing anything. That's the good news. Nothing is causing anything. If nothing is causing anything, then how do things come to be? It's very simple. Potentiality blossoms forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.17,0:03:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As actuality, when conditions permit, because of the infinite power of the field. The field is so powerful that a potentiality becomes transformed into its actuality because the power of the field is so infinite. Far beyond causality. The Newtonian paradigm of reality calibrates around 450 on the scale of consciousness. 450 is hardly sufficient to explain the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.14,0:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,existence of the universe. 450 will get you a long way. Get you to the moon. That's as far as it'll get you. And then it strains you there. Hey, God, I'm caught in the universe here. How do I get out of here? It's one planetary system after another. Did you say shut your mouth or shut your mic? Oh, I'm willing to be cut off anytime, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.59,0:04:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Come into manifestation because karmically, everything that exists is the consequence of a karmic evolution over great eons of time. And now at any moment, anything and everything and everyone represents the karmic inheritance of the past presenting to the potentiality of the present. When conditions are favorable, that potentiality becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing forces it to. Nothing causes it to. Nothing has the power to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness is like a giant electromagnetic field of infinite power. Infinite power everywhere present beyond time and space with no beginning and no ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.49,0:05:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not necessary to originate a philosophy of the beginning of God because there is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.17,0:05:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,no beginning to God. That takes care of prime cause. That which is beyond time has no beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.16,0:05:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and no ending. It has no future and it has no past. So there's nothing to be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.73,0:05:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the end of the lecture for today. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite power of the manifest arises the manifest. It's an actualization out of potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.55,0:06:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The flower unfolds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.10,0:06:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is forcing it to unfold. A little seed along the highway in Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at this incredible century plant. Stunning. Early spring it wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.62,0:06:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of June it's 12 feet high. Incredible. We found that the seed out of which it had risen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:07:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,had been lying in the dirt for 150 years. 150 years the potential lay there waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.14,0:07:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.14,0:07:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequence of barometric pressure. Sequence of moisture. Chemical constituents. A thousand variables.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.03,0:07:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then out of potentiality arose the actuality. Not because it was caused to, but because everything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then is a manifestation of a field. What you see is the action of a field. What you see, you don't see the action of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.13,0:07:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the manifestation of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.10,0:07:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all that you think you are the cause of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:07:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.94,0:08:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your karmic, what should we say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.96,0:08:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,configuration is part of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.68,0:08:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego jumps in and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.42,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.81,0:08:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it did it of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.46,0:08:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the ego jumps in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.06,0:08:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in one ten thousandths of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.08,0:08:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to claim authorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One ten thousandths of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.95,0:08:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens within one ten thousandths of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.19,0:08:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego claims ownership and authorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the way it keeps itself going
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime after lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.52,0:09:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until one day you catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught it one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.39,0:09:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Red-handed I caught it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.60,0:09:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I was in college and driving a cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And a rabbit crossed the road
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bricks went on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I caught I claiming credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.83,0:09:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But it already happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The brick had already gone on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.49,0:09:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to save the rabbit's life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.79,0:09:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in one ten thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a misunderstanding of what the Buddha taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.09,0:09:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spoken to the Buddha about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.69,0:09:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He agrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my jobs here is to correct that misquote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Eternity is glimpsed between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.28,0:10:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands of people have meditated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.66,0:10:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for probably collectively centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.64,0:10:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for the space between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.52,0:10:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a glimpse of the eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.40,0:10:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How many here have succeeded?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.72,0:10:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No one in history has succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mistranslation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.15,0:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the thought arises out of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,like a flying fish
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.45,0:10:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.91,0:10:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing arises out of nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.95,0:10:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actualization of its potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.23,0:11:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind cannot catch
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.38,0:11:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a space between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.44,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks that the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,work like billiard balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A, B, C, D, E, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.40,0:11:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks between the billiard balls
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.76,0:11:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the space between the two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the space between the two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.12,0:11:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the space between the two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.26,0:11:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.56,0:11:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there isn't any
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not a sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes from A to Z at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one arises independently
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.09,0:11:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The space you're looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.43,0:11:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is just prior to the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.40,0:11:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for the nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought begins to arise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.67,0:11:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,take form,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,pull energy to it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.45,0:11:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.81,0:11:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought arises
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like the feelingness of canineness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.11,0:11:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then dogness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the image,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then the image of dogness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.73,0:11:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then rover,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.96,0:11:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then rover got run over,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.66,0:11:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then how we all cried,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.10,0:11:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we got beaver,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:11:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and he got hit by a car too,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.94,0:12:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the whole tragic story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you're trying to find God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.64,0:12:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,instead you're rerunning an old story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.66,0:12:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Caught in the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.90,0:12:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Caught in the emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.64,0:12:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Caught in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Far from reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing to know then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.64,0:12:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is that everything is arriving,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.36,0:12:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,arising every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.32,0:12:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.22,0:12:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,acting on potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your potentiality is called karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest becomes manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by divine ordinance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.29,0:12:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The field then has the power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to actualize potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:12:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You go over to an apple tree
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.14,0:13:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you snip the stem
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.93,0:13:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the apple falls to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The apple fell to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,due to gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not due to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite power of gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.46,0:13:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,not you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.48,0:13:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that caused the apple to hit the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You release the potential,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.15,0:13:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the field is what brought forth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.05,0:13:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what you witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.18,0:13:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.85,0:13:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then from knowing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.79,0:13:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.06,0:13:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize it by, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.96,0:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no profit to lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:13:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no profit in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.74,0:14:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind cannot catch it that rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.79,0:14:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it be caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The field of the witness-observer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.30,0:14:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is faster than the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.30,0:14:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind will run along the billiard balls
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.30,0:14:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for the space between the billiard balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.50,0:14:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite space, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.66,0:14:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the actualization of potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is we become hypnotized
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.15,0:14:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and fascinated by the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,1% is like having the TV set on in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.54,0:14:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole room is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.05,0:14:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The amphitheater is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.05,0:14:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the room in the coliseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.05,0:15:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a little 4-inch TV set in the corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.05,0:15:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're focused on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, isn't this a busy coliseum?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.46,0:15:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you go away from the little 4-inch television set
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.01,0:15:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And experience the grandeur and the stillness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The coliseum at midnight and a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.42,0:15:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody there but yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you've become hypnotized
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.14,0:15:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that the mind is a nothingness, an emptiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a program going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.54,0:15:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have become hypnotized by the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hypnotized, brainwashed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.54,0:15:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to believe that that's you and that's your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.54,0:15:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we start out with those grim words
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gets better?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.54,0:16:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go through...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.49,0:16:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have never read Power vs. Force?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, please, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How have I failed Thee, Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.66,0:16:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't because you're here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.01,0:16:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.01,0:16:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the sake of those who are misfortunates,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.20,0:16:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we will put the map of consciousness up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.20,0:16:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The map of consciousness has evolved over the centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.74,0:16:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, evolved over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.78,0:16:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's collectively man's wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a modification
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from Columbia Psychoanalytic Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.10,0:16:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Below the level of 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.83,0:16:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they're called the emergency emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:16:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, they're called the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.83,0:17:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the perennial philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.93,0:17:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the wisdom of the ages revisited.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.93,0:17:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difference is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.93,0:17:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it's stratified on a calibrated scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.93,0:17:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Logarithmic scale of one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.93,0:17:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to be understood, have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.65,0:17:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular lifetime was unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.10,0:17:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In this entity speaking here now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it began at age three
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.95,0:17:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with rather stunning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.05,0:17:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,quite advanced, what the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced spiritual experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.34,0:17:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, out of nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.34,0:17:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.69,0:17:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,out of complete and total oblivion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.69,0:17:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.98,0:17:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly, stunningly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a shocking awareness of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.68,0:17:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,existence as existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,without any thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with no words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.80,0:18:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-year-old doesn't know the word existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.82,0:18:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any thinkingness involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.82,0:18:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,just the confrontation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.82,0:18:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothingness with existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.82,0:18:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which was not pleasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oblivion was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.86,0:18:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence brought up immediate problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one being,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if you exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it could have come about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would not have existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.89,0:18:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first thing that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.89,0:18:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when you identify reality as existence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,existence or nonexistence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Having spent some lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.11,0:18:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as a Hinayana Buddhist,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,negating everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.72,0:18:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I had arrived in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.58,0:18:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If the void was real, you'd stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.58,0:18:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The void is almost real,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.32,0:19:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness then arose
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the stunning confrontation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.82,0:19:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and immediately arose
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,out of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.82,0:19:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.39,0:19:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the ultimate reality nothingness or allness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.39,0:19:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the dilemma,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which you resolve at consciousness level 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.84,0:19:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.84,0:19:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothingness or allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.61,0:19:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of that mistranslation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.61,0:19:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this understanding of the Buddha's work,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is void nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no thingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's beyond form.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as it's beyond form,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.80,0:19:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing could exist
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or be known to exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,except for the infinite reality of allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.73,0:19:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness or allness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence or nonexistence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:20:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it was a weird life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.09,0:20:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And such experiences then
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.79,0:20:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with what's real,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would sit in class trying to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.79,0:20:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of self would disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.79,0:20:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,into sort of an infinite field,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.79,0:20:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would get scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.79,0:20:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would try to bring myself together
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.79,0:20:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to give my name,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.79,0:20:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm sitting in this chair, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.98,0:20:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, in adolescence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.01,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it was another exquisite experience
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of in a blizzard one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.07,0:20:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to get out of the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.07,0:20:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I got into a snowbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.07,0:20:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not in bad condition or anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.07,0:20:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just I wanted to get away from the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.23,0:20:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a blizzard,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.23,0:20:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it was pitch black,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.23,0:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,no electricity on the highway where I lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.23,0:20:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And no sooner did I make a hole
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.42,0:21:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,than when I got out of the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.42,0:21:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and an infinite presence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.42,0:21:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of such exquisite magnificence,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.42,0:21:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind melted into me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.02,0:21:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It melted into its presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.30,0:21:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite sense of love was exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.30,0:21:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.30,0:21:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind, what was the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,melts and becomes silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.90,0:21:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.90,0:21:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which I am existed before all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.90,0:21:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be in existence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.90,0:21:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,after all universes have ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.26,0:21:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.96,0:21:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.74,0:21:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the realization of the presence then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.18,0:21:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The only change in life after that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.18,0:21:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was I told the story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.18,0:22:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My father found me in the snowbank
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in this exquisite state.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.50,0:22:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to breathe,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.50,0:22:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no need to resume the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.50,0:22:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see that he believed in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought if I didn't believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he thought if I didn't breathe again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was dead, my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.64,0:22:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.64,0:22:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I didn't breathe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.64,0:22:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't reactivate the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.64,0:22:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he would go through a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.64,0:22:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling guilty that his son had died
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.64,0:22:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in a snowbank,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in a blizzard,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.64,0:22:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So he would have been saddled with guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.64,0:22:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for the rest of his days, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.47,0:22:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I love my father a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.47,0:22:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the sake of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:22:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I like,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.14,0:22:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,re-owned the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.94,0:22:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Grave error, but nevertheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.94,0:22:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I never heard of co-dependency.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.10,0:23:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Could have said it's his karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.98,0:23:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing happens several times
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.62,0:23:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.62,0:23:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when for the sake of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.62,0:23:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,one decides to reactivate the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.30,0:23:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll finish this story
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.46,0:23:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the author here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.46,0:23:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,go back into it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.46,0:23:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So I forget the sequence of events,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.46,0:23:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was brought up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.46,0:23:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely religious,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.46,0:23:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,high Episcopal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.46,0:23:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an older boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.65,0:23:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an acolyte to the bishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.65,0:23:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy soprano,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.65,0:23:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and very religious, scrupulous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.13,0:23:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to confession late Saturday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.54,0:23:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and went to the earliest communion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.54,0:23:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,on a Sunday morning possible
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.54,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave as short a possible time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.54,0:23:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in which a sin could occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.54,0:23:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A sin was a black spot on your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.54,0:23:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which God could see,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.54,0:24:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I lived in dread of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.54,0:24:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Carefully, you had to live
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.06,0:24:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when you got through confession,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.06,0:24:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,said about 10 Hail Marys,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.06,0:24:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and did the rosary.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.06,0:24:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Carefully, carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.06,0:24:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you guarded your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.06,0:24:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lived in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.06,0:24:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that a sin might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could finally get into
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.57,0:24:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seven o'clock mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.57,0:24:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,have communion,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.57,0:24:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you could relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.02,0:24:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Scrupulosity, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.16,0:24:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was told the tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.70,0:24:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the way to communion
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.70,0:24:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 29 Model A Ford
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.70,0:24:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with the top down,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.70,0:24:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and we passed a 30-foot billboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.70,0:24:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a Jansen swimming suit sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.70,0:24:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a 30-foot blonde,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.70,0:24:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,curvaceously laid out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.70,0:24:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I saw a black spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At 14, there's nothing but pure testosterone
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.25,0:24:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,running through your veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.73,0:24:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, oh God, I've sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.66,0:24:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I didn't want my folks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.66,0:25:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to know that I had sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.66,0:25:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I'm at the communion rail,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.66,0:25:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought if I take the communion
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.66,0:25:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with this spot on my soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.66,0:25:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I expected lightning to come down
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.66,0:25:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and be struck dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.23,0:25:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.23,0:25:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sipped from the cup
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.23,0:25:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and no lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.30,0:25:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why later
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.18,0:25:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.46,0:25:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's looking for God to the downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.46,0:25:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt, fear, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.66,0:25:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Downside of the scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.04,0:25:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt, sackcloth and ashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.46,0:25:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,penance, saying the rosary, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.39,0:25:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.51,0:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was walking through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.51,0:25:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,October, stunningly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.51,0:25:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.93,0:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.93,0:26:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness came the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.05,0:26:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the totality of man's suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.30,0:26:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.78,0:26:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden it was like a presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.70,0:26:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in which I witnessed and comprehended
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.70,0:26:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the totality of all of mankind's suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.70,0:26:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.98,0:26:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.61,0:26:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Staggering, shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.31,0:26:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of it is incomprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.63,0:26:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not explicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.14,0:26:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot be defined in linear terminology.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.10,0:26:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Its totality is staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.29,0:26:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.77,0:26:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,any God who would create this or allow this,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.77,0:26:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.77,0:26:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In an instant, I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.09,0:27:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Very intense atheist, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.89,0:27:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Very learned atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.89,0:27:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I could outmaneuver all the Catholic theologians.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.89,0:27:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I got straight A in theology and ethics
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.89,0:27:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.89,0:27:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't believe any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.89,0:27:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was an expert at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.78,0:27:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're going to disagree with something,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.78,0:27:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you better be an expert at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.86,0:27:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I was an atheist for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.37,0:27:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheist for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.84,0:27:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But still dedicated to ascertaining
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.84,0:27:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.84,0:27:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can truth be identified?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.84,0:27:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As a youth, while other normal children
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.29,0:27:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,were out playing stickball and jacks and wrestling,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.67,0:27:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,doing other disgusting things,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.67,0:27:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they're disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.63,0:27:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dirty fingernails and they're sticking them in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.63,0:27:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.63,0:28:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was reading Plato and the aphorisms of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.24,0:28:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,arguing Plato and Aristotle and Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.50,0:28:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates was my hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.72,0:28:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates is still my hero and worldly hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.72,0:28:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, Calabrese at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.72,0:28:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.23,0:28:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he had such a profound faith and knowledge of God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.23,0:28:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that the religions that we know about today
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.84,0:28:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't even exist in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.84,0:28:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But through the intellect then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.84,0:28:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, however Socrates got there,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.84,0:28:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates actually willingly gave up his life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of truth rather than violate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.16,0:28:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,his belief system to thine own self be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.16,0:28:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So my heroes were Socrates and Aristotle and Plato.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.74,0:28:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to figure out what that's got to do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.34,0:28:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with what I was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.34,0:28:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, I was, oh yes, I was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.01,0:28:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, oh yes, the bureaucracy made with truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.04,0:28:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I went into psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.04,0:29:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,classical psychoanalysis every day of the week for four years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.38,0:29:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,training analysts from Columbia Psychoanalytic
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.38,0:29:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and Lionel Oversee by name,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.38,0:29:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,whose analyst was Cardiner
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.38,0:29:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and Cardiner's analyst was Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.38,0:29:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud was my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.79,0:29:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you think you don't have an edible complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.79,0:29:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,let me tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.79,0:29:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You just lay down on an analyst's couch an hour a day
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.79,0:29:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,every day of the week and see what comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.79,0:29:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't have to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.79,0:29:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You recreate the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.94,0:29:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I looked through psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.94,0:29:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the post and Carl Jung and through a great psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.94,0:29:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I looked to psychoanalysis and science and medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.94,0:29:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,logic, the great books of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.94,0:29:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll calibrate later today.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.94,0:29:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked to the intellect for truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.94,0:29:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,looked into the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.94,0:29:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and became ill due to excessive stresses
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.10,0:29:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of one kind or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.10,0:30:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day I decided I was going to go deep into the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.42,0:30:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to go beyond the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to go wherever it took to find the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.49,0:30:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I went on a relentless,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.45,0:30:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean absolutely relentless,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.67,0:30:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,crashed through every belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.67,0:30:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that could be held by the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.66,0:30:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,every feeling state,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.70,0:30:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,every...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.82,0:30:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual position.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.82,0:30:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I drove right to the core of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.95,0:30:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with absolute determination
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.95,0:30:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrived in hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.62,0:30:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.59,0:30:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't going to let hell stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.59,0:30:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went through the upper layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.81,0:30:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What people call hell are the upper layers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.81,0:30:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's jacks for openers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.81,0:30:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Torture,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.81,0:30:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the body parts being torn off,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.81,0:30:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, burning stakes through your eyeball.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.81,0:30:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all child's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.81,0:31:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the top surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.42,0:31:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the scary to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.42,0:31:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not where it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.58,0:31:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.58,0:31:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,One gets into the very core of dread.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.77,0:31:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One gets to the core of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One gets to the core of despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.66,0:31:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it gets bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.86,0:31:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go past,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.21,0:31:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost like a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.21,0:31:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How Dante knew that, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.21,0:31:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dante calibrates quite high.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.21,0:31:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Dante know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.21,0:31:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.21,0:31:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain level
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.24,0:31:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you realize what hell really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.24,0:31:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Far worse than you could imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.36,0:31:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.36,0:31:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,abandon all hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.36,0:31:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ye who enter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.36,0:31:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the knowingness of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.61,0:31:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.61,0:31:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,then it gets bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.61,0:31:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The hopelessness is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.61,0:31:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness is forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.14,0:32:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing and no one to be called upon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.98,0:32:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is there any recourse.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.98,0:32:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One is in an agony of despair and hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.71,0:32:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.58,0:32:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hell of it is you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.58,0:32:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what forever means.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.06,0:32:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the eons go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.06,0:32:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.07,0:32:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the depths of that blackness,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.07,0:32:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a voice arose within and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.22,0:32:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.22,0:32:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him to help me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.26,0:32:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.34,0:32:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're hopeless and no appeal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.34,0:32:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is possible to be answered,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.34,0:32:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet a voice said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.34,0:32:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.07,0:32:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came oblivion,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.03,0:32:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total oblivion,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.60,0:32:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which lasted, I don't know how long,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.79,0:33:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in earthly time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.40,0:33:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the oblivion cleared,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.40,0:33:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.56,0:33:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the stunning magnificence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.17,0:33:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.17,0:33:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is all that exists shown forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.20,0:33:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.20,0:33:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, it disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.46,0:33:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.04,0:33:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Its exquisite beauty is paralyzing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.75,0:33:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't function in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.17,0:33:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I then did leave the world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.17,0:33:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for some many years, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.65,0:33:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.65,0:33:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the largest psychiatric practice
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.65,0:33:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.65,0:33:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,50 employees, half a dozen psychiatrists.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.65,0:33:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We had advanced research laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.42,0:33:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the first computers in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.42,0:33:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I walked away from it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.99,0:34:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I had my tools in my old truck
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.99,0:34:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and drove away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.20,0:34:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind never did return to thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.28,0:34:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence within
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.20,0:34:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests forth in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.20,0:34:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as the speakingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.20,0:34:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The speakingness is a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.20,0:34:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.20,0:34:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.13,0:34:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see, the body moves about by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.57,0:34:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that it's walking by itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see anybody making it walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.60,0:34:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it's going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.27,0:34:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.68,0:34:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.77,0:34:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It does whatever it does by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.25,0:34:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.37,0:34:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, no longer having
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.37,0:35:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the heavy burden of being
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.37,0:35:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the cause of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.50,0:35:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,your life can be one of infinite joy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.50,0:35:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.78,0:35:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's hard to stay serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.78,0:35:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll plumb more out from all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.02,0:35:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However, people do ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.24,0:35:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it like?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.24,0:35:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the experiences?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.24,0:35:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.27,0:35:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I've told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.27,0:35:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Having done my duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.59,0:35:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we will go on with the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.58,0:35:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I went to a lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.37,0:35:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by Dr. Diamond, John Diamond,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.55,0:35:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.58,0:35:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, he's an excellent teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.58,0:35:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And he gave a course on kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.90,0:35:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,applied kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.90,0:36:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And his two books,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.31,0:36:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Body Doesn't Lie
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.31,0:36:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Behavioral Kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.31,0:36:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are classics in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.50,0:36:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I watched the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.50,0:36:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.50,0:36:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the experiences I'd had,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.50,0:36:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood it in a different context.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.57,0:36:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.95,0:36:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Their life is in the Newtonian causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.95,0:36:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they saw this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.95,0:36:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they saw kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.95,0:36:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as a local phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.95,0:36:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You put a fig here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.21,0:36:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're allergic to figs,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.21,0:36:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,your arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.21,0:36:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they looked at it like fig arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.21,0:36:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause, effect, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.21,0:36:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they were seeing it as a local phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.21,0:36:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, that's ridiculous, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.21,0:36:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I could see,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.50,0:36:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what I saw was there's an infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.50,0:36:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you present to the field
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.82,0:36:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is concordant with truth or life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.82,0:36:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.65,0:36:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the life energy flows and you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.65,0:36:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In the absence of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.35,0:37:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the body goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.35,0:37:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The absence of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.77,0:37:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the world calls false,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.77,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there's dualistic opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.75,0:37:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is supportive of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.75,0:37:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is aligned with truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.30,0:37:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,energizes the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.30,0:37:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The body goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.30,0:37:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quick response.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.49,0:37:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick response.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.49,0:37:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel the energy flow down the arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.49,0:37:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you press down with two fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.62,0:37:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.94,0:37:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,elephants calibrate over 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.94,0:37:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.97,0:37:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're over 120,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.97,0:37:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the arm will go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.06,0:37:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.06,0:37:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,elephants calibrate over 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.02,0:37:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.02,0:37:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.06,0:37:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not yes and no.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.06,0:37:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's yes or not yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.25,0:37:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.87,0:38:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.90,0:38:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't an opposite to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.90,0:38:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,called falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.10,0:38:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not an opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.10,0:38:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.42,0:38:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as electricity flows down a wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.42,0:38:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's either on or it's not on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.61,0:38:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not an opposite of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.96,0:38:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,called offness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.96,0:38:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.56,0:38:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there's onness going down the wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.56,0:38:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,now there's offness going down the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.56,0:38:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.56,0:38:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.69,0:38:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there you begin to catch
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.69,0:38:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Newtonian duality is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.69,0:38:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.74,0:38:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is not a duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.92,0:38:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a singularity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.92,0:38:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed in a matter of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.92,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Which we'll explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.92,0:38:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.04,0:38:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what we discovered is that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.26,0:39:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,truth could be calibrated on a scale
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.26,0:39:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.26,0:39:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A logarithmic scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.62,0:39:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the smallest energy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.61,0:39:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of living things?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.61,0:39:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, conscious things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.61,0:39:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got it was bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.61,0:39:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria then became number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.61,0:39:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the highest consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.18,0:39:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's ever walked the planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.82,0:39:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the great avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.82,0:39:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, Krishna, Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.82,0:39:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at one thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.92,0:39:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Between bacteria
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.21,0:39:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great avatars,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.27,0:39:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.27,0:39:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all expressions of life
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.27,0:39:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can be calibrated from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.33,0:39:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This gives us a new way of looking
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.33,0:39:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.42,0:39:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Which I'd never started.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.42,0:39:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A new way of looking at the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.60,0:39:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the relative truth
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.60,0:39:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.60,0:40:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.81,0:40:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.81,0:40:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go to the calibrated levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.81,0:40:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see that from back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.19,0:40:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Golly, I can't see it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.50,0:40:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't see much anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.50,0:40:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.82,0:40:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a thingy here
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.82,0:40:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes this light up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.82,0:40:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or else it turns on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.82,0:40:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One or the other is going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.27,0:40:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.27,0:40:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.01,0:40:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My golly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.01,0:40:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.45,0:40:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So we calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.45,0:40:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,then a scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.45,0:40:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.77,0:40:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We said on a hypothetical scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.77,0:40:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,one to a thousand,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.77,0:40:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all that exists can be calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.77,0:40:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.99,0:40:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Also extends beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.99,0:40:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that everything that was true
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.14,0:40:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or supportive of life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.78,0:40:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.78,0:40:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that was false,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.10,0:40:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,non-supportive of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.10,0:40:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the absence of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.10,0:41:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.19,0:41:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have then a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.83,0:41:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything above 200
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.83,0:41:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is relative degrees of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.83,0:41:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 is falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.69,0:41:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you could calibrate anything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.69,0:41:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.69,0:41:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or ever did exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.14,0:41:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.45,0:41:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the substrate of all existence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.45,0:41:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.71,0:41:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,without which nothing could be known,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.71,0:41:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite field beyond all time,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.26,0:41:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.26,0:41:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all measure,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.70,0:41:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a giant field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.77,0:41:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which records everything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.77,0:41:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that ever existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.77,0:41:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.99,0:41:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,every passing feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.99,0:41:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how seemingly trivial,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.22,0:41:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is recorded in this infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.22,0:41:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.22,0:41:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.43,0:41:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.43,0:42:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.01,0:42:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that has ever existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.01,0:42:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,done or been happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.01,0:42:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that ever happened
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.01,0:42:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.01,0:42:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or location or space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.01,0:42:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can be retrieved
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.49,0:42:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrated right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.49,0:42:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no past.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.74,0:42:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no future.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.74,0:42:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no time dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.18,0:42:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.18,0:42:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has no ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.18,0:42:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.22,0:42:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.22,0:42:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,every hair on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.22,0:42:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,should be counted as true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.22,0:42:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The very essence of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.98,0:42:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that one does,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.98,0:42:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,every intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.98,0:42:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,most important of all is intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.49,0:42:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.49,0:42:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.29,0:42:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,like on a disc,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.67,0:42:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.49,0:42:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.49,0:42:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also scary, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.49,0:42:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it scary?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.06,0:42:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.06,0:42:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.06,0:42:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but think of all the bad thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.06,0:42:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.06,0:43:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people I've probably killed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.16,0:43:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,over the lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.58,0:43:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.58,0:43:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.67,0:43:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.50,0:43:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,good thing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.50,0:43:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,One lifetime I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.83,0:43:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.79,0:43:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember these lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.79,0:43:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.79,0:43:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was during the Crusades
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.98,0:43:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and this guy's recurred
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.98,0:43:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout a number of lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.98,0:43:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.98,0:43:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a pal of mine forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.98,0:43:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.98,0:43:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we're both warriors
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.98,0:43:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're both really good
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.98,0:43:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.98,0:43:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.21,0:43:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's your turn to be killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.21,0:43:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd better elect me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.21,0:43:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.21,0:43:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfected it many a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.21,0:43:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't transcend it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.53,0:43:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,until you master it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.91,0:43:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.91,0:43:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.91,0:43:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it was during the Crusades.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.04,0:43:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.04,0:43:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,1099 or whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.07,0:44:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a warrior for Allah
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.87,0:44:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was a warrior for Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.87,0:44:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.94,0:44:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,here we are in the Holy Lands
