Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.49,0:58:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russians, in fact, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.54,0:58:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Cold War, if they lost the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.36,0:58:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they had the infinite bomb, and they would destroy,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.52,0:58:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,destroy all of life forever on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.85,0:58:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Swell people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.59,0:59:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice thought, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.95,0:59:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.49,0:59:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how come it didn't come to pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.84,0:59:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look within the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.96,0:59:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can come up with an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's because of the sheer weight of the 15%,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.44,0:59:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it never came to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.80,0:59:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this 15%, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.54,0:59:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances the negativity of the rest of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.75,0:59:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.39,0:59:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear, hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.11,0:59:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't tell me it was going to be way back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.44,0:59:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was supposed to be right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.12,0:59:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They put it where I can't reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.56,0:59:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, this is the evolution of life on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.35,0:59:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to transcend the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.53,0:59:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's best to understand what the ego is, how it arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.53,1:00:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, having recontextualized it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.72,1:00:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that it's easy to dissolve it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.20,1:00:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas it's formidable,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.92,1:00:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to set it up as an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.68,1:00:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,become dualistically opposed to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.68,1:00:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to conquer the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.68,1:00:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you try to conquer or destroy the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.68,1:00:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, the greater the power you give it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.68,1:00:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see how life evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.97,1:00:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Life evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.97,1:00:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this galactic explosion, supposedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.36,1:00:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All this energy is whirling around in the infinite universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.76,1:00:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It finally coalesces into a lava-like hot stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.83,1:00:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,flying around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.83,1:00:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And this hot mass coalesces.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.83,1:00:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It spins around for some more billions and trillions of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.92,1:00:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It gradually cools down,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.92,1:00:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually gets a crust on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.92,1:00:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A crust on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.15,1:00:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of the Earth is still molten.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.15,1:00:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Go down that way,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.53,1:00:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's thousands of degrees inside there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.53,1:01:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.82,1:01:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're setting over 10,000 degrees of molten lava.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.82,1:01:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.62,1:01:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.77,1:01:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.48,1:01:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.48,1:01:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Has not disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.48,1:01:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still very active.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.48,1:01:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting for you down there, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.70,1:01:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally it comes up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.12,1:01:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroys whole colonies of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.12,1:01:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this molten on the surface cools down enough
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.15,1:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get a crust,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.15,1:01:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the material of life then chemically reaches a certain stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.82,1:01:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Local conditions become favorable.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.16,1:01:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.16,1:01:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in its interaction with matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.16,1:01:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is the potential for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.70,1:01:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest becomes manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.76,1:01:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the light of God arose creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.53,1:01:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of God then is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.72,1:02:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is the light of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.72,1:02:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Its power is so infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.13,1:02:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that the interaction of consciousness and matter
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.13,1:02:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,spawns life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.13,1:02:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Life then arises out of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.64,1:02:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot arise out of non-life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.96,1:02:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That is so obvious and clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.15,1:02:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how you jump categories.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.15,1:02:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say that life arose mechanically
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.21,1:02:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as a chemical accident out of non-life,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.21,1:02:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you've just violated all the laws of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.56,1:02:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've jumped from one level of abstraction to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.76,1:02:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This level of abstraction does not apply
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.76,1:02:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to this level of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.76,1:02:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The laws of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.67,1:02:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot arise out of non-life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.67,1:02:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can only arise out of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.76,1:02:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.76,1:02:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I tell it to you, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.76,1:03:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible for life to arise out of non-life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.30,1:03:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It even violates categories of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.77,1:03:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, life can only arise out of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.77,1:03:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, because of the quality and the nature of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.73,1:03:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.73,1:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.12,1:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is impossible to destroy life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.12,1:03:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think you've killed something,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.40,1:03:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you've just gone into a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.40,1:03:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot kill anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.40,1:03:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is infinite and indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.56,1:03:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.60,1:03:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the conservation of life is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.60,1:03:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.60,1:03:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.98,1:03:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could mankind have existed this long?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.98,1:03:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They know about the law of matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.98,1:03:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,energy, like matter and energy cannot be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.20,1:03:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,equals MC squared.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.20,1:04:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Man has yet to discover
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.46,1:04:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of the invincibility of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.46,1:04:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot destroy life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.87,1:04:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.87,1:04:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You swat the fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.22,1:04:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, it goes off in its etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.22,1:04:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the fly doesn't even notice it?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.22,1:04:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're weeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.01,1:04:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I've killed another being.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.01,1:04:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The fly goes on flying in its etheric body
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.44,1:04:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.44,1:04:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.44,1:04:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't even notice it, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.44,1:04:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wailing with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.44,1:04:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've killed a living thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.44,1:04:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've killed a living thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.57,1:04:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The fly doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.57,1:04:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Foams along, comes a little energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.80,1:04:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,comes back karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.80,1:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,another egg goes on flying.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.64,1:04:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, an animal doesn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To an animal, the dream world has the same reality
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.92,1:04:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.56,1:04:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you wake your cat up,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.56,1:05:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you go over to pet her, and she's annoyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.56,1:05:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.68,1:05:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because she's having a ball, and you just...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.68,1:05:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.59,1:05:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To the animal, the dream life has the same reality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.59,1:05:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as physical life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.59,1:05:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.59,1:05:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Same life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.59,1:05:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.39,1:05:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.45,1:05:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.45,1:05:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the experience of life is 100% subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.64,1:05:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All experience is subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.22,1:05:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the infinite I is subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.41,1:05:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is radical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.41,1:05:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is nothing but radical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.41,1:05:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.41,1:05:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the subjective,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.62,1:05:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you could not say that only the objective
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.07,1:05:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is real.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.07,1:05:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Radical reductionism.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.15,1:05:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanistic reductionism.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.01,1:05:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is real unless you can measure it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.36,1:06:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and weigh it, locate it in time and place.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.36,1:06:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.04,1:06:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a radically subjective statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.58,1:06:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectively, it seems that that is truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.12,1:06:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's meaningless, meaningless verbiage
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.94,1:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,unless subjectively you conclude that's truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.94,1:06:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the fact that you conclude that's truth
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.94,1:06:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't make it truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.94,1:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that to you, it's truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.12,1:06:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanistic reductionism, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.12,1:06:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,relies completely on subjectivity for its reality
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.12,1:06:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and it thereby negates its premise.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.12,1:06:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only thing that's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.34,1:06:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what is measurable in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.34,1:06:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be no way of knowing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.34,1:06:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.63,1:06:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Except for subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.63,1:06:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.24,1:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the protozoa doesn't worry about such things.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.24,1:07:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The first life is lichens.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.82,1:07:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've always wondered.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.01,1:07:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard anybody speak the word.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.01,1:07:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,L-I-C-H-E-N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.01,1:07:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that lichens or lichens?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.01,1:07:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.10,1:07:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Lichens?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.55,1:07:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've always called them lichen lichens.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.41,1:07:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, I'm correct one way or the other, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.21,1:07:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the first things.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.85,1:07:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, chlorophyll appears as a source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.85,1:07:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the misfortune of humans is that we're not green.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.07,1:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were green, we'd just walk around
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.23,1:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and automatically recharge our energy source.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.23,1:07:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And life appeared then in animal form, the protozoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.71,1:07:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the crucial point.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.18,1:07:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have within itself the source of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.18,1:08:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore it has not within itself the source of survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.18,1:08:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It must get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.18,1:08:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to get to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.48,1:08:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The animals got to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.48,1:08:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right from the protozoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.48,1:08:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the amoeba.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.48,1:08:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The amoeba has to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.34,1:08:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic law of the ego is get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.34,1:08:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.34,1:08:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes more and more clever how to get in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.60,1:08:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It joins with other getters, forms tribes, clubs,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.60,1:08:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,organizations, armies.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.95,1:08:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it starts out, the bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.95,1:08:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at calibrated level one.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.28,1:08:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Viruses are not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.28,1:08:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Viruses only reduplicate their own DNA,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.34,1:08:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.34,1:08:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not aware that they exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.34,1:08:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't experience that they exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.34,1:08:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.98,1:09:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The first conscious organism is bacteria at one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.98,1:09:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, life evolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.36,1:09:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so far back in time,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.36,1:09:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in archeologic time,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.36,1:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I can't pronounce the words.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.36,1:09:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pre-Columbia, pre-Columbia.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.36,1:09:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was killing you in Chile years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.36,1:09:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.40,1:09:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which only calibrated one, appeared,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.40,1:09:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,70% of earth time had already evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.40,1:09:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,70% of rock archeologic time had already evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.40,1:09:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After 70% of time of our universe had evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.40,1:09:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,only then did appear consciousness level one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.40,1:09:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the form of bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.40,1:09:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the first marine invertebrates
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.40,1:09:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at two.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.50,1:09:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level three.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.53,1:09:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The first fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.76,1:09:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then land life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.98,1:09:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then scorpions crawled out of the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.98,1:10:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,400 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.43,1:10:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then primitive brachiopods,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.43,1:10:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,shell-crushing sharks,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.43,1:10:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,reptiles,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.43,1:10:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.43,1:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, only in the West,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.43,1:10:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see consciousness levels slowly evolving here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.62,1:10:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and only in the West,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.62,1:10:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,2% of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.62,1:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,would be anything really meaningful to modern man.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.10,1:10:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.58,1:10:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the interesting thing, yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.44,1:10:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the core then of survival,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.44,1:10:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.44,1:10:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is your human brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.44,1:10:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is your brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.44,1:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the evolution of time then,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.01,1:10:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how consciousness evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.01,1:10:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,From a bacteria at one,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.24,1:10:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see the law of life here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.24,1:10:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,up to consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.24,1:10:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.81,1:11:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it doesn't kill anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.92,1:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When a lion eats a rabbit,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.92,1:11:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not kill the rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.92,1:11:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing is in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.92,1:11:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.98,1:11:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.36,1:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabbitness goes back into
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.19,1:11:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,its etheric representation
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.19,1:11:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a collective attractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.19,1:11:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and re-manifests as rabbitness,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.19,1:11:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but rabbit consciousness is not destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.76,1:11:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to level 200 then,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.76,1:11:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the main characteristic
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.76,1:11:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from human viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.76,1:11:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it looks,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.99,1:11:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks cruel and horrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.99,1:11:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It always has to get something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.99,1:11:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you have
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.28,1:11:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,crustaceans,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.28,1:11:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,insects,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.28,1:11:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,arachnids at seven,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.28,1:11:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,fish at 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.82,1:11:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the octopus?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.82,1:11:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Octopus is at 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.01,1:11:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharks at 24.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.30,1:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragon at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.30,1:12:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Reptiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.30,1:12:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Snakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.30,1:12:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.30,1:12:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whales.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.30,1:12:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.30,1:12:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Birds of prey.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.30,1:12:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Rhinoceros.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.46,1:12:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Polar bears.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.46,1:12:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Grizzly bears.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.46,1:12:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackals and foxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.46,1:12:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.10,1:12:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Javelina.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.10,1:12:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.29,1:12:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.29,1:12:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a shift.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.48,1:12:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.48,1:12:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly see the emergence
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.48,1:12:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.52,1:12:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,On the human levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.52,1:12:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,200 was a critical level
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.52,1:12:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,between truth and falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.58,1:12:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,between that which is supportive of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.58,1:12:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.58,1:12:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the animal world,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.58,1:12:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you see exactly the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.58,1:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.64,1:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.68,1:12:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of killing others,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.68,1:12:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you become a herbivore,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.68,1:12:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,peacefully munching the grass.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.12,1:12:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the elk at 210,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.12,1:12:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sheep,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.12,1:12:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,elephants,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.12,1:12:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,farm horses,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.12,1:12:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,cats,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.12,1:12:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,race horses,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.12,1:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,family dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.48,1:13:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.48,1:13:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.48,1:13:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the evolution of consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.34,1:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just a human affair.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.34,1:13:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the evolution of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.72,1:13:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.72,1:13:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.72,1:13:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.08,1:13:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it is only interested in me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.08,1:13:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 on now,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.56,1:13:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes less and less destructive to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.56,1:13:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The herbivore eats the grass,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.91,1:13:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fertilizes the grass,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.91,1:13:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't kill anything or anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.91,1:13:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you get up to some interesting things here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.97,1:13:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see cats and dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.97,1:13:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Cats and dogs at 240.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.97,1:13:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember the scale of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.50,1:13:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that cats and dogs calibrate higher
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.50,1:13:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,than about a large percentage of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.50,1:13:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.08,1:14:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in Toronto,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.50,1:14:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.50,1:14:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we were talking about dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.50,1:14:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.50,1:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and a dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.50,1:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.50,1:14:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A cat's purr calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.24,1:14:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we love them so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.24,1:14:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,People worship their cats and their dogs
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.24,1:14:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't like people.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.24,1:14:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to think they were weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.24,1:14:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they make sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.24,1:14:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you came from her family,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.87,1:14:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd rather be with a dog or a cat too,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.87,1:14:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.87,1:14:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all backbiting,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.03,1:14:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,vicious,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.03,1:14:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and greedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.03,1:14:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you adopt an animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.21,1:14:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of the animal
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.21,1:14:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,jumps five or ten points.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.21,1:14:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Strangely enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.45,1:14:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.45,1:14:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.45,1:14:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat's purr is 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.45,1:14:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we were in Toronto,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.45,1:14:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the front page of the paper,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.45,1:14:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we were up there to give a lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.45,1:14:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a dog named Elvis.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.45,1:15:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And out in a park,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.16,1:15:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,out in a park,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.16,1:15:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a slightly mentally imbalanced man.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.16,1:15:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a whole bunch of high-powered rifles,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.25,1:15:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,6,000 rounds of ammunition.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.44,1:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a mass killer,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.44,1:15:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.44,1:15:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he was just gonna mow down people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.44,1:15:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.05,1:15:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody could deter him,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.05,1:15:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and he,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.05,1:15:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.05,1:15:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,he's fully armed.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.05,1:15:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got all kinds of weapons.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.05,1:15:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a walking,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.05,1:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,walking army all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.05,1:15:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody could talk to him
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.05,1:15:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or get near him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.15,1:15:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.15,1:15:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this dog with a frisbee in his mouth
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.37,1:15:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,runs over to this guy
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.37,1:15:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and wants to play with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.37,1:15:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jumps up with his frisbee,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.37,1:15:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and this dog's name is Elvis.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.44,1:15:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's on the front page of the paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.44,1:15:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And when Elvis approached this mad killer
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.44,1:15:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who was about to mow everybody down
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.44,1:15:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and commit suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.44,1:15:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this guy changed his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.85,1:15:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's love at 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.85,1:15:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.85,1:15:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart shocker,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.85,1:15:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly the guy said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.85,1:16:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.85,1:16:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.85,1:16:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And he put down his weapons
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.85,1:16:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and went for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.85,1:16:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That was on the front page of the paper
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.98,1:16:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the very day we gave the lecture on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.98,1:16:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Very funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.98,1:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the cat's purr,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.98,1:16:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the dog's wagging tail,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.98,1:16:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm interested in,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.98,1:16:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm interested in talking parrots.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.68,1:16:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's a famous one, Alex,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.68,1:16:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you've probably seen on the History Channel
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.68,1:16:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or Discovery Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.68,1:16:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex is a trained African Grey,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.68,1:16:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 401.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.68,1:16:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco, the trained gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.68,1:16:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 405.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.68,1:16:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, can animals think?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.68,1:16:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you watch a crow figure out,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.78,1:16:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta pick this up,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.78,1:16:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,use it as a tool,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.78,1:16:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,use it as a lever,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.78,1:16:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course they can think.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.78,1:16:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what do you think he's doing there?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.78,1:16:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He's obviously thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.78,1:16:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.81,1:16:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, then, you're in a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.81,1:16:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At 400, you're capable of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.94,1:16:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have the good fortune now,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.94,1:17:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a friend of us, a friend of ours,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.94,1:17:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,gave us an African Grey parrot.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.94,1:17:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're finding out
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.39,1:17:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,whether this is all true or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.39,1:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see where she's at this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.03,1:17:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.03,1:17:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli, when we got her eight weeks ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.16,1:17:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated over, let's see, 325,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.28,1:17:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,340, 335, 340.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.64,1:17:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli calibrated at 335.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.64,1:17:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.64,1:17:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli now, we've had for a couple months,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.76,1:17:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over at 335, 340, 345,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.76,1:17:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,342, 343, 342.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.80,1:17:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so Broccoli's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.80,1:17:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has gone ahead seven points
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.80,1:17:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just in a couple of months
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.80,1:17:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,through the human interaction
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.80,1:17:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and love and caringness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.80,1:17:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how we affect the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.80,1:17:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how the field affects others.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.80,1:17:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.08,1:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what can I do to help this planet?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.08,1:17:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them, keep off the streets.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.95,1:18:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Approach everything lovingly with goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.03,1:18:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See the sacredness and the beauty of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.40,1:18:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To be kind to all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.72,1:18:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To be loving and kind towards all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.94,1:18:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.94,1:18:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already doing all you can do.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.94,1:18:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already raising
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.94,1:18:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.94,1:18:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the level of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.16,1:18:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is like the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.16,1:18:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we, by combined intention then,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.84,1:18:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,raise the overall level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.84,1:18:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we lift all the ships in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.84,1:18:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Little organizations that try to lift this ship
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.09,1:18:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have quite a job.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.12,1:18:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it slips back as fast as you can lift it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.12,1:18:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by lifting the sea effortlessly,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.19,1:19:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all that float in the sea are lifted equally.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.19,1:19:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And to which it has no resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.22,1:19:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you use force, they will resist you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.22,1:19:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you lift the sea, they cannot resist it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.54,1:19:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll take a break,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.54,1:19:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll see you right after.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.54,1:19:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I just explained the figure of the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.24,1:19:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,while you folks were talking.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.24,1:19:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The dilemma of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.33,1:19:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,once you understand the structure of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.78,1:19:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion is an automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.81,1:19:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.81,1:19:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain information is in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.16,1:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,transformational.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.16,1:19:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.98,1:19:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.98,1:19:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is represented in the human brain today.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.98,1:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the difficulty was,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.36,1:20:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when humans evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.36,1:20:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the prefrontal cortex was plastered
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.75,1:20:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.75,1:20:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.97,1:20:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the old animal brain wasn't silenced
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.72,1:20:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and substituted by an advanced consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.72,1:20:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.82,1:20:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced consciousness was now
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.04,1:20:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,plastered onto the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.04,1:20:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you walk around with a spiritual conscience
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.12,1:20:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the emotions of an animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.34,1:20:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want a super fix to be a human being,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.34,1:20:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we all get extra credit for having done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.04,1:20:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was St. Peter, I'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.40,1:20:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,where were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.40,1:20:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.39,1:20:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.39,1:20:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.35,1:21:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That does nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.35,1:21:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do all kinds of karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.35,1:21:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.50,1:21:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you're in the squash
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.98,1:21:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,between animal drive
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.98,1:21:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and intelligence and spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.01,1:21:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So self-hatred then becomes endemic.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.01,1:21:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's intolerable,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.56,1:21:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it now becomes projected onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.56,1:21:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And hatred then tends to run
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.65,1:21:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the social world,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.65,1:21:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,political world,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.65,1:21:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.28,1:21:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The projection of that self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.28,1:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you understand that the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.67,1:21:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,animal in you,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.67,1:21:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of your enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.15,1:21:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,should be adopted.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.15,1:21:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's my ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.24,1:21:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.72,1:22:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we adopt the pet within us.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.10,1:22:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.35,1:22:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we hate people who cut in front of us
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.35,1:22:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in traffic, don't we, Ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.35,1:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we hate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.35,1:22:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They should die.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.35,1:22:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They should die.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.35,1:22:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They deserve death.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.86,1:22:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be killed,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.49,1:22:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,tortured,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.49,1:22:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and blown away.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.49,1:22:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.52,1:22:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.03,1:22:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.34,1:22:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good boy, Ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.60,1:22:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of guilt, penance,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.95,1:22:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth, and ashes,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.95,1:22:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which hasn't really worked,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.95,1:22:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can tell by today's headlines,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.36,1:22:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion for the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.18,1:22:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of the Ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.18,1:22:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing that the Ego's primordial drive
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.18,1:22:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is to continue existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.18,1:23:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it thinks the only way it can continue to exist
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.18,1:23:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is by getting.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.18,1:23:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the human drive
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.50,1:23:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to constantly get more, more,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.50,1:23:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,more money, more prestige, more power,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.56,1:23:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,more windows in your office,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.56,1:23:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a bigger, longer, better car,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.56,1:23:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.33,1:23:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, until the late 1980s,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.33,1:23:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the paradigm consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.20,1:23:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was 90 at the time of the birth of Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.20,1:23:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of the birth of Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.97,1:23:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.97,1:23:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,overall was 100.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.38,1:23:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the Middle Ages,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.38,1:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the Inquisition all up until
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.08,1:23:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the late 1980s,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.72,1:23:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the overall level of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.72,1:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.40,1:23:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see, integrity and truthfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.40,1:24:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.65,1:24:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is pride, gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.65,1:24:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in the late 1980s,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.12,1:24:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at about the time of the Harmonic Concordance,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.12,1:24:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.12,1:24:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,jumped from 190 to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.35,1:24:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us remember that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.89,1:24:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,People around the world prayed at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.89,1:24:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level jumped to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.27,1:24:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It stayed at 205 until October of last year,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.52,1:24:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when it suddenly went from 205 to 207,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.52,1:24:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,again at the time of the Harmonic Concordance.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.52,1:24:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Life at 190 is different than life at 205,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.38,1:24:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly different than 207,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.36,1:24:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're talking about a logarithmic scale,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.36,1:24:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,not arithmetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.68,1:25:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,207 is a lot more powerful than 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.68,1:25:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's changed the paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.96,1:25:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in which I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.96,1:25:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional America,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.96,1:25:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born right after World War I,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.96,1:25:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,went through World War II, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.96,1:25:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, success was
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.37,1:25:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,status, money, house, car, title, position.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.37,1:25:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, then, what counts is success
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.03,1:25:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a worldly term.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.24,1:25:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the ethics of successful business was,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.24,1:25:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, a few things could be swept under the carpet.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.24,1:25:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The old boy network worked, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.34,1:25:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,190.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.66,1:25:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we saw the collapse of the Enron and WorldCom
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.69,1:25:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.69,1:25:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did they collapse?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.72,1:26:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because they were non-integrists,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.72,1:26:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because the consciousness of mankind had moved to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.72,1:26:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, they would still be successful corporations.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.72,1:26:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See, what you can get away with at 190,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.11,1:26:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't get away with at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.11,1:26:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So now the new paradigm of success is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.11,1:26:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's Martha Stewart on the carpet for?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.20,1:26:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Not money. Integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.20,1:26:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for taking a stock tip,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.07,1:26:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but for lying to the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.07,1:26:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She's in jail for lying.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.07,1:26:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for whatever the financial thing was,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.03,1:26:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that was just the incident, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.22,1:26:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, we're interested in integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.22,1:26:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's integrity that counts now,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.22,1:26:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and all we look for in others and in employees
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.22,1:26:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and in companies, if we invest in a stock,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.38,1:26:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to know what is this level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.38,1:26:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the integrity of this corporation?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.48,1:26:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the new measure of success is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.98,1:27:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can make money. It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.46,1:27:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell anybody how to double your income in no time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.46,1:27:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can double everybody's income in no time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.32,1:27:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it. I did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.03,1:27:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of working 40 hours a day,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.21,1:27:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.21,1:27:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You work 80. It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.84,1:27:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As an intern, I worked 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.84,1:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As a resident, I worked 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.00,1:27:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started in practice, I worked 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.32,1:27:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's simple. You double your income, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.32,1:27:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make money sitting home watching TV, eating popcorn.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.48,1:27:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you need a second job. Simple. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.40,1:27:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the new paradigm now is integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.40,1:27:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because the consciousness level of mankind is 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.40,1:27:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that women executives,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.04,1:27:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,corporations run by women executives,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.04,1:27:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Fortune magazine,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.04,1:28:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,outdid those run by men executives in 2003.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.04,1:28:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.59,1:28:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Women executives try harder.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.51,1:28:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But another thing is they don't belong to the old boy network.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.76,1:28:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the old boy network, a few little,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.05,1:28:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay you off for this, you pay me off for that,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.05,1:28:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is understood.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.53,1:28:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call it? Mordida, you know, the payoff, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.12,1:28:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The women weren't engaged in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.54,1:28:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Women are scrupulously honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.54,1:28:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pain in the neck.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.96,1:28:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This form is supposed to be filed with this on,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.96,1:28:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so you think, oh, jeez, we haven't filed it in 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.96,1:28:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.96,1:28:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it says right here, this is supposed to be filed
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.96,1:28:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with the post office, and you say, oh, God, help us.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.16,1:28:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So women are more integrous, you might say, in business,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.16,1:29:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're newer at the game, they're on trial,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.96,1:29:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're art-performing men in the corporate world, for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.72,1:29:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In due time, they'll be the old girl network.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.23,1:29:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mildred, I'll lend you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.23,1:29:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Dorothy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.23,1:29:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But they haven't been in it long enough
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.23,1:29:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the old girl network going yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.23,1:29:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they won't, because in a world at 207,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.48,1:29:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe that a few bucks under the counter will not happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.48,1:29:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But the women right now are leading the pack.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.93,1:29:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go back to where we were.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.09,1:29:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.60,1:29:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then through the advancement of the levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.63,1:29:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.63,1:29:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world are important
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.63,1:29:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're the intellectual,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.63,1:30:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the jewels of man's thing throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.11,1:30:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,From 350 B.C.,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.11,1:30:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle, Socrates, Plato,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.22,1:30:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,on down to the modern time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.22,1:30:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.60,1:30:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was put together by Mortimer Adler
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.60,1:30:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at the University of Chicago, I think back in the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.60,1:30:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the good luck to come upon a whole set.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.50,1:30:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how they calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.50,1:30:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.50,1:30:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see they're all in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.50,1:30:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I keep thinking this is a TV controller.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.50,1:30:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.50,1:30:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you see they all calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.98,1:30:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mid to high 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.98,1:30:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.98,1:30:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One or two go as far as 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.27,1:30:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names of all, all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.27,1:30:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The great inventors, the great geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.44,1:30:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Euclid, Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.44,1:30:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.44,1:30:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kant, Kantian categories.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.44,1:31:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,John Locke, Shakespeare, Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.80,1:31:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates is not on there
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.00,1:31:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because Socrates didn't write any books.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.00,1:31:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But Socrates calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.38,1:31:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the great thinkers of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.60,1:31:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it ends with Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.60,1:31:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud and Einstein are both at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.92,1:31:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein couldn't shift paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.92,1:31:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at 499, at 500, you shift paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.92,1:31:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s is the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.92,1:31:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the level of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.21,1:31:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the primordial reality
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.21,1:31:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is not whether a thing is logical,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.21,1:31:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but whether it's loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.21,1:31:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So lovingness, the spiritual realm,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.21,1:31:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,really shows up from 500 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.21,1:31:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and up is the level of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.21,1:31:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you move from
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.21,1:31:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,describable scientific objectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.37,1:31:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.37,1:32:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality is all subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.01,1:32:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is a spiritual reality cannot be proven.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.68,1:32:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable belongs
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.68,1:32:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,within the intellectual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.68,1:32:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you cannot demand or expect
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.22,1:32:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,any kind of spiritual reality to be provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.22,1:32:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were provable,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.22,1:32:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't be a spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.22,1:32:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be an intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.64,1:32:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.64,1:32:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing for our world,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.92,1:32:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,our world,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.21,1:32:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, of course, discovered the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.21,1:32:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrates at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.98,1:32:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When science moved into quantum,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.98,1:32:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum science,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.11,1:32:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.11,1:32:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was the big advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.27,1:32:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery that the mere act of observation
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.27,1:33:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,already changes the changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.32,1:33:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do the same experiment twice
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.48,1:33:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because having observed it the first time,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.48,1:33:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already collapsed the wave function
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.48,1:33:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've collapsed it to the new,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.48,1:33:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to a new paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.96,1:33:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.96,1:33:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was the stunning,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.96,1:33:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.96,1:33:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,metaphysical confrontation
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.96,1:33:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.63,1:33:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Einstein bucked at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.63,1:33:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrates it the same as Freud at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.92,1:33:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And Einstein said,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.92,1:33:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer to believe that there is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.92,1:33:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,an independent objective reality out there
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.92,1:33:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists independent of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.92,1:33:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And he refused to walk through the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.92,1:33:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore he stayed at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.92,1:33:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Freud refused to accept
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.92,1:33:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.92,1:33:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung, who calibrates at 520,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.92,1:33:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,included the human spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.92,1:33:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as part of the experiential reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.92,1:33:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrates at 520.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.92,1:33:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,David Bohm calibrates at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.68,1:34:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was able to include
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.68,1:34:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the extension of,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.68,1:34:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he was able to make the jump
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.68,1:34:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that Einstein couldn't make.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.68,1:34:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.84,1:34:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the historic antecedents
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.84,1:34:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of our culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.84,1:34:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,our culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.88,1:34:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,our academic culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.88,1:34:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the paradigm of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.88,1:34:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that has stood the test of time
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.88,1:34:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,since 350 BC at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.88,1:34:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see, unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.88,1:34:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a couple of errants in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.88,1:34:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing calibrates at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.88,1:34:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you remove Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.88,1:34:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.36,1:34:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Marx's error?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.36,1:34:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx's error,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.36,1:34:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget I was a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.55,1:34:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for 50 years, psychoanalyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.55,1:34:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time in the early,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.80,1:34:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,first part of the 1800s,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.80,1:34:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel was the predominant
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.80,1:34:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.80,1:34:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Karl Marx had an unresolved
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.12,1:35:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,edible complex,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.12,1:35:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,resented his authority,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.44,1:35:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and threw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.44,1:35:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.44,1:35:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't like Hegel's
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.44,1:35:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,principle of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.44,1:35:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle of the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.12,1:35:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is the whole basis for the calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.12,1:35:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.12,1:35:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All these calibrated levels,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.12,1:35:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated are in comparison
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.12,1:35:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.40,1:35:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.40,1:35:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is divinity and God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.46,1:35:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.72,1:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx substituted then a dualistic
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.07,1:35:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,perception of reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.07,1:35:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which has been fatal to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.07,1:35:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the perpetrator-victim model.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.52,1:35:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator-victim model
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.52,1:35:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality calibrates about 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.58,1:35:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's caused,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.58,1:35:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,no, Marx was at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.41,1:35:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's caused to mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.41,1:35:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has been in my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.41,1:35:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million people dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.82,1:35:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You think philosophy
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.82,1:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is an academic practice?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.92,1:35:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.92,1:36:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The dualistic conception,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.71,1:36:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which sees everything in terms
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.71,1:36:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of perpetrator and victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.71,1:36:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is a rejection from res interna,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.71,1:36:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and they think you see it in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.71,1:36:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It brought down 100 million people.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.08,1:36:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Death to 100 million people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.08,1:36:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at philosophic error.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.17,1:36:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So philosophy is hardly
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.17,1:36:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,an intellectual
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.36,1:36:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dry academic study.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.36,1:36:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The very basis upon which
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.36,1:36:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind makes its decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.36,1:36:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see perpetrator-victim
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.56,1:36:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as a duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.56,1:36:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can project it into anything
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.56,1:36:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.93,1:36:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you believe that it's out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.22,1:36:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all in your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.28,1:36:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no perpetrators
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.44,1:36:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are no victims out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.44,1:36:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.44,1:36:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything is manifesting
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.44,1:36:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,its own innate potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.63,1:36:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A company goes to town,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.63,1:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or I saw it in
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.11,1:37:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thiensville, Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.11,1:37:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A company comes to town.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.90,1:37:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The town people are very rural,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.25,1:37:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hardly have any money.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.25,1:37:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this big canning company comes in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.60,1:37:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly the whole town thrives.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.60,1:37:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People got new cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.60,1:37:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People can buy books, clothes, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.60,1:37:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The company makes money.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.15,1:37:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People who own the stock are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.31,1:37:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.72,1:37:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Until somebody comes in and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.72,1:37:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator-victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.23,1:37:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've destroyed the community.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.23,1:37:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's happy and thriving.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.55,1:37:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the company living off the worker?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.66,1:37:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are the workers living off the company?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.33,1:37:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The company was poor
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.42,1:37:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,before it got to Thiensville.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.42,1:37:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people in Thiensville
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.45,1:37:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,were poor before the company got there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.45,1:37:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not see that as a mutuality
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.19,1:37:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of a duality?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.96,1:38:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are good for the company
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.40,1:38:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the company is good for the town.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.40,1:38:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not see it as a mutuality?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.72,1:38:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as mutuality
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.38,1:38:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't sell hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.38,1:38:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.38,1:38:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't sell hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.38,1:38:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can stir you all up
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.38,1:38:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that the employees are screwing the company
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.38,1:38:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or the other way around
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.73,1:38:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the company is screwing the employees
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.73,1:38:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now with my leverage of hate
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.73,1:38:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make a
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.82,1:38:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,vocation for myself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.52,1:38:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and profit off the conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.52,1:38:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what happens with the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.65,1:38:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that dualistic
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.84,1:38:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,error
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.29,1:38:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of perpetrator-victim
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.32,1:38:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which now pervades our society
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.32,1:38:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and shreds it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.32,1:38:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees everything as perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.32,1:38:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention anything
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.32,1:38:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but somebody doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.87,1:38:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have a parade about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.87,1:39:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it right we should have
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.21,1:39:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,men's and women's bathrooms
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.21,1:39:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,separately? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.21,1:39:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.28,1:39:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to France, they don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.28,1:39:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we could have a men's and women's bathroom rights.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.28,1:39:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.79,1:39:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to France, there's just one
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.79,1:39:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,place and you go in.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.82,1:39:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Men and women.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.82,1:39:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so divisiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.11,1:39:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then divisiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.11,1:39:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and conflict originates
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.11,1:39:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,within the mind and then gets projected
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.11,1:39:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.11,1:39:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but the consequences are grave.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.11,1:39:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million people
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.27,1:39:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have died
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.27,1:39:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,due to that falsity
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.27,1:39:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that duality
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.27,1:39:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,projected from the mind of Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.27,1:39:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,135 is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.62,1:39:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,far from truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.94,1:39:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's move
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.10,1:39:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.93,1:39:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want people to see that philosophy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.93,1:39:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is not some academic thing.
